eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Religious and faith-based leaders from all walks of life gathered at the Cape Town international convention centre. To pray over donated bottled water that will be dispatched to flood victims in KwaZulu-Natal as part of humanitarian assistance by NGO Gift Of The Givers. READ: Shembe Church assists KZN flood-affected areas The organisation’s founder, Doctor Imitiaz Sooliman says the support has been overwhelming and encourages more people to lend a helping hand eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports in the video above.